01:13.241 --> 01:15.876
- OBVIOUSLY, YOU'RE NOT UP
ON YOUR GAY FILM HISTORY.

01:15.909 --> 01:18.112
WHAT EVER HAPPENED
TO BABY JANE?

01:18.146 --> 01:19.847
STARRING THE TWO GREATEST
BITCH GODDESSES

01:19.880 --> 01:21.782
IN THE HISTORY
OF THE HUMAN RACE:

01:21.815 --> 01:24.452
MISS JOAN CRAWFORD
AND MISS BETTE DAVIS.

01:24.485 --> 01:28.256
"MS. CRAWFORD AND I
NE-E-EVER GOT ALONG."

01:28.289 --> 01:30.858
- I NE-E-EVER SAW IT.

01:30.891 --> 01:33.394
- I SUPPOSE THERE'S NO POINT
EVEN MENTIONING ESTHER BLODGETT.

01:33.427 --> 01:36.130
- I KNOW THAT ONE.
IT'S A STAR IS BORN, RIGHT?

01:36.164 --> 01:39.333
- OH, THANK GOD.
HE REALLY IS GAY.

01:39.367 --> 01:41.869
- EAT.
- NO THANKS.

01:41.902 --> 01:43.604
- IT'S TUNA SALAD,
NOT PARAKEET.

01:43.637 --> 01:45.206
- I'M NOT HUNGRY.

01:45.239 --> 01:46.407
- WELL, YOU'RE GOING
TO NEED YOUR STRENGTH.

01:46.440 --> 01:49.210
- [scoffs]
FOR WHAT?

01:49.243 --> 01:51.912
THE DOCTOR SAYS
I MIGHT HAVE A PERMANENT LIMP.

01:51.945 --> 01:54.148
THAT SHOULD
BRIGHTEN UP MY ACT.

01:54.182 --> 01:55.749
- WHAT ARE YOU LISTENING
TO THE DOCTORS FOR?

01:55.783 --> 01:58.352
AFTER THEY STUFFED MY BRAIN
BACK INTO MY HEAD,

01:58.386 --> 01:59.820
THEY TOLD ME
I'D NEVER DRAW AGAIN.

01:59.853 --> 02:02.823
- AND DO YOU?
- YES...

02:02.856 --> 02:06.394
FOR ABOUT 15 MINUTES,
THEN MY HAND STARTS TO SHAKE,

02:06.427 --> 02:08.496
SO I USE A COMPUTER.

02:08.529 --> 02:09.697
BUT THE POINT IS--

02:09.730 --> 02:11.232
- YOU WENT ON!

02:11.265 --> 02:14.335
- RIGHT.
SO WILL YOU.

02:17.805 --> 02:20.908
- YOU'RE SO...

02:20.941 --> 02:24.378
REASONABLE.

02:24.412 --> 02:25.846
I KEEP HOPING
WHEN THEY CATCH MY BASHERS,

02:25.879 --> 02:27.815
THEY'LL SENTENCE THEM
TO LIFE IN PRISON,

02:27.848 --> 02:31.252
AND THEY'LL GET FUCKED NIGHTLY
BY PRISONERS WITH AIDS.

02:31.285 --> 02:32.653
- THAT'S GRUESOME.

02:32.686 --> 02:36.290
- DOESN'T COST ANYTHING
TO DREAM.

02:37.958 --> 02:42.263
WHEN IT HAPPENED TO YOU,
WEREN'T YOU ANGRY?

02:42.296 --> 02:44.398
- I TRIED
NOT TO THINK ABOUT IT.

02:44.432 --> 02:47.968
- I CAN'T STOP
THINKING ABOUT IT.

02:48.001 --> 02:50.438
I SEE THEIR FACES,

02:50.471 --> 02:54.275
THEIR BOOTS
SMASHING INTO ME.

02:54.308 --> 02:57.311
I EVEN HUGGED THIS ONE GUY'S
FOOT TO MY STOMACH,

02:57.345 --> 03:01.482
HOPING IT'D STOP HIM
FROM KICKING ME.

03:01.515 --> 03:03.684
IT DIDN'T.

03:03.717 --> 03:05.953
- IF YOU'RE STILL
HOLDING ONTO THAT BOOT,

03:05.986 --> 03:08.889
THEN YOU'RE STILL
ON THE GROUND TAKING IT.

03:10.658 --> 03:12.560
FORGET ABOUT IT.
- LISTEN, IF YOU'D BEEN

03:12.593 --> 03:15.829
REDUCED TO JERKING OFF
WITH YOUR LEFT HAND,

03:15.863 --> 03:17.898
YOU'D WANT THEM DEAD TOO.

03:17.931 --> 03:22.870
[laughs]

03:22.903 --> 03:25.839
- [groans]

03:25.873 --> 03:28.309
- WHAT'S THE MATTER, BABY?
TUMMY ACHE?

03:28.342 --> 03:29.877
- [groans]

03:29.910 --> 03:32.580
- WHAT IS IT, MICHAEL,
A MIGRAINE?

03:32.613 --> 03:34.982
- IMPACTED WISDOM TEETH.
UGH.

03:35.015 --> 03:37.718
- BUT YOU HAD THEM ALL
EXTRACTED.

03:37.751 --> 03:39.320
- EMMETT DOESN'T
KNOW THAT.

03:39.353 --> 03:40.454
- [scoffs]
- OH.

03:40.488 --> 03:42.390
- WHAT POSSESSED ME?

03:42.423 --> 03:44.458
WHY DID I EVER AGREE
TO GO WITH HIM?

03:44.492 --> 03:46.327
- BECAUSE YOU'RE
A GOOD-HEARTED HUMAN BEING

03:46.360 --> 03:47.995
WHO WOULD DO ANYTHING
FOR HIS FRIEND.

03:48.028 --> 03:49.997
- CAUSE I'M
A LAME-BRAINED DOORMAT

03:50.030 --> 03:51.399
WHO DOESN'T KNOW
HOW TO SAY NO.

03:51.432 --> 03:53.334
- IT'LL ONLY BE
A COUPLE OF DAYS.

03:53.367 --> 03:55.035
- FEELS MORE LIKE
AN ETERNITY.

03:55.068 --> 03:57.505
- WE'VE DISCUSSED THESE RADICAL
FAIRY GATHERINGS IN MY CLASS.

03:57.538 --> 03:59.407
THIS GUY, HARRY HAY...

03:59.440 --> 04:00.941
- I'VE HEARD OF HIM.
- STARTED THEM IN THE '70s.

04:00.974 --> 04:02.343
THEY'RE SUPPOSED TO BE
A VERY EMPOWERING

04:02.376 --> 04:04.011
AND ENLIGHTENING EXPERIENCE.

04:04.044 --> 04:06.480
- WELL, IF THEY'RE SO EMPOWERING
AND ENLIGHTENING,

04:06.514 --> 04:07.748
WHY DON'T YOU GO?

04:07.781 --> 04:10.484
- I HAVE CLASSES,
THERE'S HUNTER.

04:10.518 --> 04:13.487
ANYWAY, EMMETT ASKED YOU,
NOT ME.

04:13.521 --> 04:16.524
- I'M NOT GOING.
NO WAY, NO WAY.

04:16.557 --> 04:18.392
- DARREN ASKED ME
TO THANK YOU

04:18.426 --> 04:19.793
FOR ALL THE FOOD
YOU'VE SENT HIM, DEB.

04:19.827 --> 04:21.629
- THE POOR KID.
IT'S THE LEAST I CAN DO.

04:21.662 --> 04:22.963
- HOW'S HE DOING?

04:22.996 --> 04:24.498
- I'M AFRAID
IT'S GOING TO BE A WHILE

04:24.532 --> 04:26.500
BEFORE SHANDA LEER
APPEARS IN PUBLIC AGAIN.

04:26.534 --> 04:28.702
- WELL, AT LEAST HE HAS
ONE RAY OF SUNSHINE IN HIS LIFE.

04:28.736 --> 04:30.938
- TELL HIM WE'LL MISS HIM
AT THE CENTER TONIGHT,

04:30.971 --> 04:35.643
BUT WE'RE GOING TO MAKE SURE
THIS NEVER HAPPENS AGAIN.

04:35.676 --> 04:37.044
- HI, EM.

04:37.077 --> 04:39.380
- UGH.

04:39.413 --> 04:42.450
- WELL, ARE YOU READY
TO FIND YOUR INNER FAIRY?

04:42.483 --> 04:44.718
- WHEN I DO, I JUST HOPE
HE LOOKS MORE LIKE TINKER BELL

04:44.752 --> 04:46.086
THAN CAPTAIN HOOK.
[laughter]

04:46.119 --> 04:47.388
- [groans]
- [scoffs]

04:47.421 --> 04:48.689
- YOU ALL PACKED?

04:48.722 --> 04:53.427
- EM, I--
- UH, BEFORE YOU SAY ANYTHING...

04:53.461 --> 04:54.828
AS WE ALL KNOW,
I HAVE BEEN

04:54.862 --> 04:56.997
GOING THROUGH SOME
PRETTY TOUGH TIMES LATELY.

04:57.030 --> 05:00.401
I GUESS YOU COULD SAY
MY HEADLIGHTS ARE ON LOW BEAM,

05:00.434 --> 05:04.672
BUT IF THIS FAIRY FROLIC
WILL TURN THE BRIGHTS BACK ON,

05:04.705 --> 05:07.441
WELL, WHAT THE FUCK,
I'LL GIVE IT A TRY.

05:07.475 --> 05:10.611
- MORE POWER TO YOU,
SWEETHEART.

05:10.644 --> 05:14.014
- WHATEVER HAPPENS,
THE IMPORTANT THING IS,

05:14.047 --> 05:19.420
I WILL ALWAYS--ALWAYS
BE GRATEFUL THAT YOUR SON,

05:19.453 --> 05:23.724
YOUR BOYFRIEND,
MY BEST PAL

05:23.757 --> 05:28.662
WILL BE THERE WITH ME,
OFFERING HIS LOVE AND SUPPORT.

05:40.741 --> 05:41.975
- [clears throat]

05:42.009 --> 05:44.578
WELL, WE'D BETTER
GET A MOVE ON,

05:44.612 --> 05:45.879
OR ELSE THESE FAIRIES
WON'T GET THEIR WINGS.

05:45.913 --> 05:48.115
- [squeals]

05:48.148 --> 05:49.617
[pats on the back]

05:50.884 --> 05:53.754
- BYE, HONEY.
- BYE.

05:53.787 --> 05:58.526
- BYE, HONEY.
[laughs]

05:59.793 --> 06:02.630
[laughter]

06:02.663 --> 06:05.666
- SO IT WAS ACTUALLY
A GOOD THING

06:05.699 --> 06:08.001
I LEFT HERE THAT NIGHT.

06:08.035 --> 06:09.903
SEE, MY--MY CONDO
NEEDED DUSTING.

06:09.937 --> 06:11.539
I DON'T REALLY TRUST
MY CLEANING LADY,

06:11.572 --> 06:16.076
AND, UH, IT GAVE ME TIME
TO THINK...

06:16.109 --> 06:19.513
ABOUT WHERE I SHOULD BE
AND WHAT I SHOULD BE DOING.

06:19.547 --> 06:23.183
SO I CAME BACK.

06:23.216 --> 06:25.419
ALTHOUGH
IT HASN'T BEEN EASY,

06:25.453 --> 06:27.020
AND EVERY DAY'S
BEEN A CHALLENGE.

06:27.054 --> 06:28.889
- BUT YOU DID IT.

06:28.922 --> 06:32.960
- YEAH, AND NOW IT'S TIME
FOR ME TO LEAVE...

06:32.993 --> 06:36.897
WITH CLEAR EYES
AND MY HEAD HELD HIGH.

06:36.930 --> 06:38.832
[sighs]

06:38.866 --> 06:42.503
GUESS THAT'S WHAT HAPPENS
WHEN YOU HAVE A GREAT COUNSELOR.

06:42.536 --> 06:44.037
AND YOUR HEALTH INSURANCE
RUNS OUT.

06:44.071 --> 06:46.039
[laughter]

06:46.073 --> 06:48.108
- YOU'LL BE BACK.

06:48.141 --> 06:50.177
- WHAT DID YOU SAY,
JONATHAN?

06:50.210 --> 06:52.913
- I SAID HE'LL BE BACK.

06:52.946 --> 06:55.683
- WELL, SURE, FOR GROUP,
AS AN OUTPATIENT.

06:55.716 --> 06:58.586
- I MEAN BACK USING,
AND THEN BACK HERE.

06:58.619 --> 07:00.654
- JESUS, JONATHAN,
CAN'T YOU BE POSITIVE?

07:00.688 --> 07:02.990
- [chuckles]
WELL, I'M THAT TOO.

07:03.023 --> 07:04.792
DOESN'T MEAN I HAVE TO LAUGH
AT BILLY CRYSTAL HERE

07:04.825 --> 07:06.660
DOING HIS STAND-UP.

07:06.694 --> 07:07.828
IT'S NOT GOING TO BE
ANY DIFFERENT FOR YOU

07:07.861 --> 07:08.962
THAN IT IS
FOR THE REST OF US.

07:08.996 --> 07:10.531
- YOU'RE WRONG.

07:10.564 --> 07:13.133
- AH, YOU'LL FIND OUT
SOON ENOUGH.

07:13.166 --> 07:15.869
IT'S NOT THE SAME WORLD YOU LEFT
WHEN YOU CAME HERE.

07:15.903 --> 07:19.573
- I'M GOING TO BE ALL RIGHT.
I'LL MAKE SURE OF IT.

07:19.607 --> 07:23.577
- WELL, JUST IN CASE,
WE'LL LEAVE A LIGHT ON FOR YOU.

07:26.580 --> 07:28.482
- IT'S AN INTERESTING OFFER.

07:28.516 --> 07:29.617
- IT'S A FIRST-RATE COMPANY,
MR. KINNEY.

07:29.650 --> 07:30.818
YOU'D FIT RIGHT IN.

07:30.851 --> 07:32.720
- INTERESTING
IN THAT THEY THINK

07:32.753 --> 07:34.021
I'D ACTUALLY AGREE TO IT.

07:34.054 --> 07:36.824
2/3 OF WHAT I WAS
PREVIOUSLY MAKING,

07:36.857 --> 07:39.092
A LESSER TITLE,
AND NO PROFIT SHARING

07:39.126 --> 07:40.694
UNTIL THE FIFTH YEAR?
MMM.

07:40.728 --> 07:42.262
- TIMES ARE TOUGH, MR. KINNEY.
IT'S A JOB.

07:42.295 --> 07:45.232
- UH, YOU MEAN
INDENTURED SERVITUDE.

07:45.265 --> 07:47.100
- THEN YOU'RE PASSING?

07:47.134 --> 07:49.737
- YOU CAN TELL THEM
I'VE JUST TAKEN A NEW POSITION.

07:49.770 --> 07:51.104
BYE-BYE.

07:51.138 --> 07:52.906
- I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU JUST DID THAT.

07:52.940 --> 07:55.275
- FLIPPED YOU ON YOUR BACK?
- FLIPPED OFF THAT HEADHUNTER.

07:55.308 --> 07:59.613
- I CAN DO BETTER.
- DOING WHAT?

07:59.647 --> 08:01.782
- WORKING FOR MYSELF
INSTEAD OF OTHER PEOPLE.

08:01.815 --> 08:03.584
- BUT ALL YOUR CLIENTS
TURNED YOU DOWN.

08:03.617 --> 08:05.252
- FUCK 'EM.
I'LL GET OTHERS.

08:05.285 --> 08:07.588
- WHAT IF YOU CAN'T?

08:07.621 --> 08:09.757
YOU'LL BE DESTITUTE.
YOU'LL HAVE NOTHING.

08:09.790 --> 08:12.125
- SINCE WHEN DID YOU
TURN INTO A JEWISH MOTHER?

08:12.159 --> 08:13.927
OR MICHAEL?

08:13.961 --> 08:16.730
- YOU'RE JUST TAKING
AN AWFULLY BIG RISK, THAT'S ALL.

08:16.764 --> 08:21.669
- WELL,
WHAT'S ONE MORE?

08:21.702 --> 08:26.874
BESIDES, IF I DON'T DO THIS NOW,
I NEVER WILL.

08:26.907 --> 08:31.144
[indistinct chatter]

08:31.178 --> 08:34.181
- SOMETHING TELLS ME
WE'RE NOT IN PITTSBURGH ANYMORE.

08:34.214 --> 08:37.918
- SOMETHING TELLS ME WE'RE
NOT EVEN ON THE PLANET ANYMORE.

08:41.321 --> 08:43.691
- YOU TWO MUST BE VIRGINS.

08:43.724 --> 08:47.094
- OKAY, HAVEN'T BEEN A VIRGIN
SINCE I WAS 15.

08:47.127 --> 08:48.696
- WELL, MAYBE OUT THERE,
BUT HERE,

08:48.729 --> 08:52.332
YOUR LIFE AS A FAIRY
HAS JUST BEGUN.

08:52.365 --> 08:53.901
I'M PERIWINKLE,

08:53.934 --> 08:56.837
THE QUEEN REGISTRAR
AND OFFICIAL GREET-AR.

08:56.870 --> 08:58.772
- "PERIWINKLE"?

08:58.806 --> 09:01.108
- IT'S MY FAIRY NAME.
EVERYONE HERE HAS ONE.

09:01.141 --> 09:03.176
- WHAT'S WRONG
WITH OUR REAL NAMES?

09:03.210 --> 09:05.646
- REAL NAMES ARE FINE
FOR THE REAL WORLD,

09:05.679 --> 09:07.915
BUT THIS IS A SPECIAL PLACE.

09:07.948 --> 09:10.183
THIS IS A MAGICAL PLACE

09:10.217 --> 09:12.686
WHERE YOU LEAVE
YOUR REAL LIFE BEHIND...

09:12.720 --> 09:15.055
[chimes ringing]

09:15.088 --> 09:16.657
AT LEAST
FOR A LITTLE WHILE.

09:16.690 --> 09:20.093
SO TAKE YOUR TIME,
GIVE IT SOME THOUGHT.

09:20.127 --> 09:21.962
IT'LL BE YOUR FAIRY NAME
FOREVER.

09:21.995 --> 09:23.196
- OOH.

09:23.230 --> 09:25.065
- SO GET SETTLED
INTO YOUR CABIN.

09:25.098 --> 09:27.801
DINNER'S WHENEVER SPIRAL AND ELK
QUIT BRAIDING HAIR

09:27.835 --> 09:29.603
AND START BOILING
GARBANZOS.

09:29.637 --> 09:32.673
OH.

09:32.706 --> 09:35.342
THERE'S A MIDNIGHT MASSAGE
IN THE YURT.

09:35.375 --> 09:38.646
YOU DON'T WANT TO MISS THAT.

09:40.247 --> 09:41.949
- WHAT'S A YURT?

09:41.982 --> 09:43.684
- IF WE BACK UP REAL SLOW,

09:43.717 --> 09:45.118
NO ONE WILL EVEN KNOW
WE WERE HERE.

09:45.152 --> 09:49.957
- HEY, YOU DRAGGED ME HERE.
WE'RE STAYING.

09:49.990 --> 09:51.959
BESIDES, WHAT'S THE WORST
THAT COULD HAPPEN?

09:51.992 --> 09:53.827
- THAT.

09:53.861 --> 09:55.696
- I'M LOOKING SO FORWARD TO THAT
TANTRIC SEX SEMINAR TODAY.

09:55.729 --> 09:57.698
- OH, ME TOO.
I THINK IT'S GOING TO BE GREAT.

09:57.731 --> 09:59.700
- COULD YOU PASS ME
THE SHOVEL PLEASE?

09:59.733 --> 10:01.234
- WE'LL START
WITH A NEW LOGO,

10:01.268 --> 10:04.705
THEN LAUNCH AN AGGRESSIVE
AD CAMPAIGN IN THE LOCALS,

10:04.738 --> 10:06.907
AND SET UP SOME
HIGH-PROFILE SPONSORSHIPS.

10:06.940 --> 10:09.242
- THAT SOUNDS BIGGER
THAN WE CAN HANDLE.

10:09.276 --> 10:11.745
- IT'S SIMPLE BRANDING.

10:11.779 --> 10:13.714
- OUR CUSTOMERS
AREN'T INTO BRANDING.

10:13.747 --> 10:15.983
TATTOOS, PIERCINGS MAYBE.
- [laughs]

10:16.016 --> 10:18.151
I'M TALKING
ABOUT A NEW IMAGE.

10:18.185 --> 10:19.720
- I ADORE MAKEOVERS,

10:19.753 --> 10:25.158
BUT OUR AD BUDGET'S
ONLY $200 A MONTH.

10:25.192 --> 10:29.897
- GREAT, THEN WE'LL RUN
A LEAN CAMPAIGN.

10:29.930 --> 10:31.732
NO FAT.

10:31.765 --> 10:34.702
- JUST LIKE OUR CUSTOMERS.
PERFECT.

10:38.772 --> 10:40.207
- JUST BETWEEN US,
AROUND HERE,

10:40.240 --> 10:42.142
WE REFER TO JONATHAN
AS "D" AND "G."

10:42.175 --> 10:44.044
- DOLCE AND GABBANA?
- [laughs]

10:44.077 --> 10:46.046
NO, DOOM AND GLOOM.
- [chuckles]

10:46.079 --> 10:48.782
OH, HE DOESN'T BOTHER ME.
- THAT'S GOOD.

10:48.816 --> 10:50.450
TO BE HONEST,
HE'S NOT ENTIRELY WRONG.

10:50.483 --> 10:53.186
A LOT OF PATIENTS DO WIND UP
COMING BACK HERE.

10:53.220 --> 10:54.788
- NOT ME.

10:54.822 --> 10:56.957
- WELL, JUST REMEMBER
WHAT WE TALKED ABOUT.

10:56.990 --> 10:59.793
- YEAH, GIVE MYSELF TIME
TO ADJUST.

10:59.827 --> 11:02.930
- AND NOT JUST YOU,
BUT THE PEOPLE IN YOUR LIFE

11:02.963 --> 11:05.933
ARE GOING TO NEED
SOME TIME TOO.

11:09.469 --> 11:12.840
HERE WE ARE.

11:12.873 --> 11:16.443
- [chuckles]

11:16.476 --> 11:18.946
NEVER THOUGHT I'D BE SO SCARED
TO SEE A DOOR.

11:18.979 --> 11:21.849
- DON'T THINK OF IT
AS A DOOR.

11:21.882 --> 11:25.919
THINK OF IT AS A THRESHOLD...

11:25.953 --> 11:28.221
TO A NEW LIFE.

11:28.255 --> 11:30.190
- RIGHT.

11:30.223 --> 11:34.862
LOOK, I WANT TO THANK YOU
FOR...EVERYTHING.

11:34.895 --> 11:37.931
- YOU DON'T HAVE TO THANK ME.
YOU DID IT ALL.

11:37.965 --> 11:40.968
- WITH YOUR HELP.

11:43.871 --> 11:48.475
- LISTEN,
I-I WAS WONDERING IF I--

11:48.508 --> 11:50.343
WELL...

11:50.377 --> 11:53.280
I COULD GIVE YOU
A CALL SOMETIME--

11:53.313 --> 11:55.282
I MEAN, STRICTLY
ON A PROFESSIONAL BASIS.

11:55.315 --> 11:57.117
YOU KNOW, LIKE,
I SUDDENLY FIND MYSELF

11:57.150 --> 11:59.887
STANDING ON A LEDGE WITH A ROPE
AROUND MY NECK, OR SOMETHING.

11:59.920 --> 12:03.323
- OR MAYBE
JUST TO SAY HELLO?

12:07.127 --> 12:12.032
- * IT'S NOT AN EASY THING

12:12.065 --> 12:17.037
* TO FIND YOU CAN'T GO ON

12:17.070 --> 12:18.505
- [sighs]

12:18.538 --> 12:23.043
- * POINT OF RECKONING,
TO NOT BE STRONG *

12:23.076 --> 12:27.314
*

12:27.347 --> 12:32.385
* WHEN YOU CAN BARELY STAND

12:32.419 --> 12:37.190
* IT'S HARD TO TAKE A HAND

12:37.224 --> 12:42.262
* IT NEVER GOES AS PLANNED,
BUT ALL ALONG *

12:42.295 --> 12:45.398
- GOOD LUCK.

12:45.432 --> 12:48.268
- * I GUESS YOU KNEW THAT

