- RECOGNIZE THIS?

13:10.190 --> 13:13.026
- OH, YES.
REMSON PHARMACEUTICAL ACCOUNT.

13:13.060 --> 13:14.094
MY LAST CAMPAIGN.

13:14.127 --> 13:15.562
- BEFORE THE OLD WARRIOR

13:15.595 --> 13:18.598
WAS UNCEREMONIOUSLY ESCORTED
FROM THE BUILDING

13:18.631 --> 13:21.368
WITHOUT SO MUCH AS A...
both: BALLPOINT PEN.

13:21.401 --> 13:23.904
- SO WHAT DOES
THIS MAGIC PILL DO?

13:23.937 --> 13:26.206
- WELL, IT'S GUARANTEED
TO TURN YOU INTO A HOTTIE

13:26.239 --> 13:27.507
WHO CAN CLIMB THE MATTERHORN.

13:27.540 --> 13:29.509
IT ALSO REDUCES
YOUR VIRAL LOAD.

13:29.542 --> 13:31.945
WHAT ARE YOU
SHOWING IT TO ME FOR?

13:31.979 --> 13:34.114
- VANCE IS TAKING YOUR IDEA

13:34.147 --> 13:36.216
AND PITCHING IT
TO REMSON TOMORROW.

13:36.249 --> 13:38.451
- WELL, HE SHOULD.
HE OWNS IT.

13:38.485 --> 13:40.954
- BUT YOU THOUGHT IT UP.

13:40.988 --> 13:44.191
- BASIC RULE OF ADVERTISING
AND ETERNAL DAMNATION:

13:44.224 --> 13:47.060
ONCE YOU SELL YOUR SOUL
TO THE DEVIL,

13:47.094 --> 13:48.628
HE HOLDS THE COPYRIGHT.

13:48.661 --> 13:50.597
- SO COME UP
WITH ANOTHER IDEA.

13:50.630 --> 13:53.066
- AND THEN YOU CAN STEAL
THE ACCOUNT FROM VANCE,

13:53.100 --> 13:54.935
AND YOUR FORMER ASSISTANT
ALONG WITH IT.

13:54.968 --> 13:56.203
- WELL, THAT'S
AN INGENIOUS PLAN, CYNTHIA.

13:56.236 --> 13:57.938
- [giggles]

13:57.971 --> 13:59.606
- BUT WHAT PHARMACEUTICAL
COMPANY IS GOING TO TRUST

13:59.639 --> 14:01.608
THEIR WONDER WEAPON
TO A ONE-MAN BAND

14:01.641 --> 14:03.110
WORKING OUT OF HIS HOUSE?

14:03.143 --> 14:04.277
- IT'S NOT THE SIZE
THAT MATTERS.

14:04.311 --> 14:05.478
- HAVE I TAUGHT YOU
NOTHING?

14:05.512 --> 14:07.347
- IT'S THE VISION.

14:07.380 --> 14:09.883
IF YOU CAN WIN THIS ACCOUNT,
THEN YOU'LL BE BACK ON TOP.

14:09.917 --> 14:11.952
- [laughs]

14:11.985 --> 14:17.290
FOR ONCE,
I'LL STICK TO THE BOTTOM.

14:17.324 --> 14:20.127
- YOU HAVE TO THROW OFF
YOUR CIVILIAN DRAG

14:20.160 --> 14:24.564
AND BECOME TRUE FAIRIES,
OR ELSE THE MAGIC DOESN'T WORK.

14:24.597 --> 14:27.400
YOU'D LOOK ENCHANTING
IN THIS.

14:27.434 --> 14:29.169
- STRAPLESS MAKES ME
LOOK FAT.

14:29.202 --> 14:31.104
- WELL, THEN USE
YOUR OWN DIVINE POWERS

14:31.138 --> 14:33.106
AND COME UP WITH SOMETHING
FABULOUS.

14:33.140 --> 14:35.008
- FROM THESE SCHMATTAS?

14:35.042 --> 14:36.643
- EVERY FAIRY
HAS A GOD-GIVEN GIFT

14:36.676 --> 14:39.980
TO TAKE WHAT'S UGLY AND MAKE IT
INTO SOMETHING BEAUTIFUL.

14:40.013 --> 14:41.548
[chimes ring]

14:41.581 --> 14:44.251
YOU'LL SOON DISCOVER
THAT YOU CAN DO THAT TOO.

14:44.284 --> 14:47.420
NOW, I REALLY MUST FLY.
I'M LATE FOR AN EAR-CANDLING.

14:47.454 --> 14:49.456
IF YOU CARE TO JOIN ME,
IT'S DOWN BY THE BOG.

14:49.489 --> 14:51.024
- WHERE'S THE BOG?

14:51.058 --> 14:54.027
- MAKE A LEFT AT THE YURT.

14:55.295 --> 14:57.664
- WHEN I AGREED
TO COME HERE WITH YOU,

14:57.697 --> 15:00.533
I DIDN'T AGREE
TO LOOK LIKE MY MOTHER.

15:00.567 --> 15:03.003
- WELL, MAYBE
PERIWINKLE'S RIGHT.

15:03.036 --> 15:05.672
IF WE PUT SOMETHING ON,
WE'LL...

15:05.705 --> 15:07.941
FEEL THE MAGIC.

15:07.975 --> 15:13.013
I LOOK LIKE VIRGINIA MAYO
IN SOUTH SEA WOMAN.

15:13.046 --> 15:15.615
YOU KNOW, LET'S JUST FORFEIT
OUR REGISTRATION FEE

15:15.648 --> 15:17.050
AND GO HOME.

15:17.084 --> 15:19.286
- NOW YOU TELL ME?

15:19.319 --> 15:21.154
I LOOK COMPLETELY
AND UTTERLY--

15:21.188 --> 15:22.489
- HOT!

15:22.522 --> 15:27.060
TOTALLY HOT.

15:27.094 --> 15:31.298
- IT'S JUST A LITTLE SOMETHING
I PICKED OFF THE RACK.

15:31.331 --> 15:33.433
- I'M PISTON.
- I'M WOLFEN.

15:33.466 --> 15:36.169
- I'M...

15:36.203 --> 15:38.338
DUMPLING.

15:38.371 --> 15:41.574
- HELLO, DUMPLING.

15:41.608 --> 15:43.510
- SEE YA LATER, DUMPLING.

15:43.543 --> 15:47.314
- "DUMPLING"?
WHERE'D YOU GET THAT?

15:47.347 --> 15:49.749
- IT SUDDENLY CAME TO ME.

15:49.782 --> 15:52.185
- YOO-HOO!
WANNA PLAY?

15:52.219 --> 15:55.122
- COME ON.
- COME AND PLAY, COME ON.

15:55.155 --> 15:57.190
- THAT MUST BE
THE NAKED VOLLEYBALL GAME.

15:57.224 --> 15:59.592
- YOUR POWERS OF OBSERVATION
ARE REMARKABLE.

15:59.626 --> 16:01.194
- OKAY, LET'S GO.

16:01.228 --> 16:07.100
[laughter and chatter]

16:08.635 --> 16:10.403
- LET'S CHECK IT OUT.

16:10.437 --> 16:12.772
- YOU'RE NOT SERIOUS.
- WELL--EH, COME ON.

16:12.805 --> 16:14.607
IT MIGHT BE FUN.

16:14.641 --> 16:19.346
- YOU GO AHEAD, I'LL STAY HERE
AND SHAKE MY POM-POMS.

16:19.379 --> 16:24.751
[chatter]

16:24.784 --> 16:27.020
- AND WE'RE THANKFUL THAT YOU
CAME OUT TO SEE US TONIGHT.

16:27.054 --> 16:29.222
NOW, AS YOU KNOW,
THE POLICE ARE STILL WORKING

16:29.256 --> 16:32.125
TO APPREHEND THE THREE MEN
WHO ATTACKED DARREN EALY.

16:32.159 --> 16:34.494
- IN THE MEANTIME, WE'VE MET
WITH A LIAISON OFFICER

16:34.527 --> 16:36.363
WHO'S ASKED US
TO KEEP A LOOKOUT

16:36.396 --> 16:38.365
FOR ANYONE MATCHING
THEIR DESCRIPTIONS,

16:38.398 --> 16:40.100
AND TO TAKE EXTRA PRECAUTIONS

16:40.133 --> 16:42.435
WHEN WE'RE OUT ON THE STREET,
ESPECIALLY AT NIGHT.

16:42.469 --> 16:44.404
- KEEPING THAT IN MIND,
WE'D LIKE TO OPEN THE FLOOR

16:44.437 --> 16:47.140
TO YOUR SUGGESTIONS
ON HOW TO MAKE LIBERTY AVENUE

16:47.174 --> 16:49.809
A SAFER ENVIRONMENT
FOR ALL OF US.

16:49.842 --> 16:51.778
YES?

16:51.811 --> 16:54.114
- I NEVER THOUGHT
I'D SAY THIS,

16:54.147 --> 16:57.250
BUT THE FIRST THING WE NEED
IS MORE COPS ON THE STREET.

16:57.284 --> 16:59.052
- WE'VE ALREADY TALKED
TO THE NEW POLICE CHIEF.

16:59.086 --> 17:00.587
HE SAID HE'D DO HIS BEST.
- YEAH, SURE.

17:00.620 --> 17:02.422
WE'VE ALL HEARD THAT ONE
BEFORE.

17:02.455 --> 17:04.424
- THEN LET'S SEND A PETITION
TO THE MAYOR,

17:04.457 --> 17:05.792
DEMANDING
SOMETHING BE DONE.

17:05.825 --> 17:07.194
- WE ALSO NEED
SOME MORE LIGHTING,

17:07.227 --> 17:08.561
ESPECIALLY
ON THE SIDE STREETS.

17:08.595 --> 17:10.730
- GOOD IDEA.
WE'LL TAKE NOTE OF THAT.

17:10.763 --> 17:12.299
YES?

17:12.332 --> 17:13.333
- I THINK WE SHOULD
WEAR LITTLE WHISTLES

17:13.366 --> 17:14.534
AROUND OUR NECKS.

17:14.567 --> 17:15.602
THAT WAY,
IF SOMEONE ATTACKS US,

17:15.635 --> 17:17.470
ALL WE HAVE TO DO IS BLOW.

17:17.504 --> 17:19.606
- [whistles]

17:19.639 --> 17:21.808
[crowd murmurs]

17:21.841 --> 17:25.145
LIKE THAT?

17:25.178 --> 17:27.547
- WOULD YOU LIKE
TO SAY SOMETHING?

17:27.580 --> 17:29.816
- WELL, WHO DO YOU THINK
WILL COME RUNNING?

17:29.849 --> 17:31.551
THEM?
[scoffs]

17:31.584 --> 17:33.553
THEY CAN'T EVEN
DEFEND THEMSELVES.

17:33.586 --> 17:35.588
THE COPS?

17:35.622 --> 17:37.690
IF A BUNCH OF HOMO-HATERS WANT
TO BEAT THE SHIT OUT OF YOU,

17:37.724 --> 17:39.826
YOU'RE NOT GOING TO STOP THEM
BY BLOWING A LITTLE WHISTLE.

17:39.859 --> 17:42.162
- THEN WHAT DO YOU SUGGEST?

17:42.195 --> 17:45.165
- WE PROTECT OURSELVES.

17:45.198 --> 17:46.433
PATROL THE STREETS.

17:46.466 --> 17:48.335
- YOU MEAN
A VIGILANTE GROUP?

17:48.368 --> 17:50.303
- YEAH, THE PINK POSSE.

17:50.337 --> 17:52.705
- ISN'T THAT TAKING THE LAW
INTO YOUR OWN HANDS?

17:52.739 --> 17:55.208
- WHICH LAW IS THAT?

17:55.242 --> 17:57.177
THE ONE THAT SAYS
YOU CAN'T GET MARRIED?

17:57.210 --> 17:59.312
THAT IF THEY FIND OUT
YOU'RE GAY,

17:59.346 --> 18:00.780
THEY CAN FIRE YOUR ASS?

18:00.813 --> 18:02.715
THAT YOU CAN'T ADOPT KIDS?

18:02.749 --> 18:05.852
HELL, THEY CAN EVEN
ARREST YOU FOR FUCKING.

18:05.885 --> 18:07.720
- THAT WAS CHANGED.
- RIGHT.

18:07.754 --> 18:09.722
YOU CAN NOW COPULATE
IN TEXAS.

18:09.756 --> 18:12.859
WELL, YIPPIE-KI-YO-KI-AY!

18:12.892 --> 18:14.661
[crowd laughing and murmuring]

18:14.694 --> 18:16.463
- SHH, SHH, SHH, SHH.
- ALL RIGHT, OKAY, OKAY, OKAY.

18:16.496 --> 18:18.265
OKAY,
LET'S HAVE SOME ORDER.

18:18.298 --> 18:21.468
- YOU THINK ANYONE WOULD DARE
CALL A BLACK MAN A NIGGER?

18:21.501 --> 18:24.371
AND TRY CALLING AN ISRAELI
A KIKE.

18:24.404 --> 18:27.507
MAN, THEY'D BLOW YOUR ASS
RIGHT OFF THE FACE OF THE EARTH.

18:27.540 --> 18:28.741
[scattered chatter]

18:28.775 --> 18:31.511
BUT THEY HAVE NO PROBLEM
CALLING US FAGS.

18:31.544 --> 18:33.880
WHY?

18:33.913 --> 18:35.615
BECAUSE THEY CAN.

18:35.648 --> 18:37.217
[crowd murmuring]

18:37.250 --> 18:38.785
BECAUSE THEY KNOW
WE'RE ALL SISSIES,

18:38.818 --> 18:42.889
THAT WE'RE TOO CHICKENSHIT
TO DO ANYTHING.

18:42.922 --> 18:47.627
SO GO ON, SIGN YOUR PETITIONS
AND WRITE YOUR LETTERS

18:47.660 --> 18:49.762
AND BLOW
YOUR LITTLE WHISTLES,

18:49.796 --> 18:54.267
BUT NOTHING'S GOING TO CHANGE
UNTIL YOU FIGHT BACK.

18:54.301 --> 18:58.238
UNTIL YOU LEARN TO SAY,
"DON'T FUCK WITH ME!"

18:58.271 --> 19:04.211
[crowd murmuring]

19:11.618 --> 19:13.553
- HEY, DID YOU SEE THIS?

19:13.586 --> 19:15.522
THEY ACTUALLY CAUGHT
THE FUCKING BASHERS.

19:15.555 --> 19:17.290
- MMM.
WOW, THAT'S FANTASTIC.

19:17.324 --> 19:18.458
- WOULDN'T IT BE WONDERFUL
IF, FOR ONCE,

19:18.491 --> 19:19.926
JUSTICE WERE ACTUALLY SERVED?

19:19.959 --> 19:21.294
- YEAH, WELL, I'D LOVE
TO SERVE IT TO THEM,

19:21.328 --> 19:22.929
RIGHT DOWN
THEIR FUCKING THROATS.

19:22.962 --> 19:24.797
- IT'S ALL THANKS
TO DARREN'S DESCRIPTION.

19:24.831 --> 19:26.266
- I BET HE MUST
FEEL RELIEVED.

19:26.299 --> 19:27.800
- MORE LIKE BLOODTHIRSTY.

19:27.834 --> 19:29.336
- WELL, WE ALL KNOW
THERE'S NOTHING MORE TERRIFYING

19:29.369 --> 19:30.570
THAN A BLOODTHIRSTY
DRAG QUEEN.

19:30.603 --> 19:32.339
[laughs]

19:32.372 --> 19:34.407
- HEY, DEB,
HOW ABOUT A CUP OF COFFEE?

19:34.441 --> 19:36.743
- SURE, HONEY,
HAVE A SEAT, I'LL BE--

19:36.776 --> 19:38.545
TEDDY.
HI, HONEY!

19:38.578 --> 19:40.213
all: TED!

19:40.247 --> 19:41.314
- WE MISSED YOU!

19:41.348 --> 19:43.216
- OH, HOW ARE YOU DOING?

19:43.250 --> 19:44.217
- I'M DOING GREAT.

19:44.251 --> 19:47.287
- AH, YOU LOOK GOOD.

19:47.320 --> 19:49.622
- WELL, SO WHAT'S NEW?

19:49.656 --> 19:52.825
- I JUST GOT OUT OF REHAB.

19:52.859 --> 19:55.995
- HOW DID IT GO?

19:56.028 --> 19:58.431
- IT WAS PROBABLY
THE MOST SIGNIFICANT EXPERIENCE

19:58.465 --> 19:59.732
OF MY LIFE.

19:59.766 --> 20:01.301
YEAH, THE FIRST DAY
I WAS THERE,

20:01.334 --> 20:04.337
I WAS TOTALLY RESISTANT,
FURIOUS, ASHAMED,

20:04.371 --> 20:06.005
CERTAIN I DIDN'T
BELONG THERE.

20:06.038 --> 20:08.641
THE SECOND DAY,
I STARTED TO ACCEPT THEIR HELP,

20:08.675 --> 20:12.312
WENT TO GROUP
AND INDIVIDUAL SESSIONS.

20:12.345 --> 20:13.980
I BEGAN SHARING THE PAIN,
YOU KNOW.

20:14.013 --> 20:15.482
[bell dings]
- HEY, DEB!

20:15.515 --> 20:16.716
- THE THIRD DAY,
I THOUGHT THAT MAYBE I--

20:16.749 --> 20:18.585
- HONEY, SORRY,
I'D LOVE TO STAY

20:18.618 --> 20:20.019
FOR THE WHOLE SEVEN DAYS,
BUT I'VE GOT A GRILLED CHEESE

20:20.052 --> 20:21.521
THAT'S ABOUT TO TURN TO CEMENT.
[laughs]

20:21.554 --> 20:23.523
- OH, OKAY.
- WELCOME HOME.

20:23.556 --> 20:24.991
- I'VE GOT TO GET BACK
TO THE GALLERY.

20:25.024 --> 20:26.859
- OKAY, BYE.
- I'D LOVE TO HEAR MORE,

20:26.893 --> 20:27.927
BUT GUS IS WAITING
AT DAYCARE.

20:27.960 --> 20:30.897
- OKAY.
BYE.

20:34.801 --> 20:36.869
DON'T YOU HAVE
SOMEWHERE TO BE?

20:36.903 --> 20:40.640
- THANKS FOR REMINDING ME.
WELCOME BACK.

20:43.510 --> 20:47.246
- WELL I, FOR ONE, THINK YOU'RE
TO BE COMMENDED, THEODORE.

20:48.681 --> 20:50.883
- WELL, THANK YOU, BRIAN.

20:50.917 --> 20:53.019
- WHAT YOU'VE ACCOMPLISHED
IS AN AMAZING ACHIEVEMENT.

20:53.052 --> 20:54.654
- OH, I WOULDN'T GO
SO FAR AS--

20:54.687 --> 20:57.657
- TO SINK SO LOW.

20:57.690 --> 21:00.893
TO HIT BOTTOM
WITH SUCH A RESOUNDING THUD.

21:00.927 --> 21:02.662
- YOU KNOW, YOU SHOULD BE
A GUEST MOTIVATIONAL SPEAKER

21:02.695 --> 21:03.696
IN REHAB.

21:03.730 --> 21:04.764
- OF COURSE, THE GOOD NEWS IS,

21:04.797 --> 21:06.065
ONCE YOU'VE HIT THE BOTTOM,

21:06.098 --> 21:07.900
YOU CAN'T GO ANY LOWER,
SO THAT MEANS

21:07.934 --> 21:11.338
THERE'S ONLY ONE WAY TO GO,
AND THAT WAY IS...

21:13.840 --> 21:16.543
SOUNDS LIKE...

21:16.576 --> 21:18.978
- UP?
- [sips coffee]

21:32.459 --> 21:34.527
- WE CAN DO A CROSS-POLLINATION
CAMPAIGN WITH TORSO.

21:34.561 --> 21:35.995
- [grunts]
- A NEW MEMBERSHIP HERE

21:36.028 --> 21:37.697
GETS YOU 10% OFF THERE.

21:37.730 --> 21:41.734
200 BUCKS OF CLUB WEAR THERE
GETS YOU 10% OFF HERE.

21:41.768 --> 21:44.537
- SOUNDS LIKE
AN INTERESTING IDEA.

21:44.571 --> 21:46.639
I'LL GET BACK TO YOU.

21:47.707 --> 21:50.076
- HELLO.

21:50.109 --> 21:52.745
- IT'S BATMAN
AND THE NEW ROBIN.

21:52.779 --> 21:54.747
- BETTER NOT TELL
THE OLD ROBIN THAT.

21:54.781 --> 21:56.949
JUST GOT HUNTER
A MEMBERSHIP.

21:56.983 --> 21:58.951
- YEAH, YOU WANT TO HOOK UP
IN THE STEAM ROOM?

21:58.985 --> 22:01.888
- YEAH, HE SHOULD FIT IN
HERE JUST FINE.

22:01.921 --> 22:03.823
- WE DID NOT COME HERE
SO YOU COULD HIT ON THE GUYS.

22:03.856 --> 22:05.091
THAT INCLUDES BRIAN.

22:05.124 --> 22:06.359
WE CAME SO YOU
COULD STAY HEALTHY.

22:06.393 --> 22:07.960
- TOO LATE FOR THAT.

22:07.994 --> 22:10.430
- NO, IT'S NEVER TOO LATE
TO GET IN SHAPE.

22:10.463 --> 22:13.600
- YEAH, YOU WANT TO DEVELOP THAT
SIX-PACK BEFORE YOU DRINK IT.

22:13.633 --> 22:15.435
I COULD USE THAT
FOR THE AD.

22:15.468 --> 22:17.570
- WHY WORK OUT WHEN I CAN
TAKE SOME MEDS AND KA-POW!

22:17.604 --> 22:19.606
SO LONG, VIRUS.
- BECAUSE IT'S BETTER

22:19.639 --> 22:21.774
TO BUILD YOUR IMMUNE SYSTEM
NATURALLY.

22:21.808 --> 22:23.610
- GUY LOOKS PRETTY HEALTHY
TO ME.

22:23.643 --> 22:24.877
- THAT'S NOT WHAT HIV
LOOKS LIKE,

22:24.911 --> 22:26.513
AND THE MEDS
DON'T FIX ANYTHING.

22:26.546 --> 22:27.847
THEY BUY YOU TIME
IF THEY WORK,

22:27.880 --> 22:29.382
AND THEN THERE ARE
DOZENS OF SIDE-EFFECTS:

22:29.416 --> 22:32.585
SKIN RASHES, LIVER FAILURE,
CARDIAC ARREST.

22:32.619 --> 22:35.488
- A LITTLE EARLY TO BE FREAKING
THE KID OUT, DON'T YOU THINK?

22:35.522 --> 22:36.989
- I JUST DON'T WANT HIM
BELIEVING SOME MISLEADING AD

22:37.023 --> 22:38.525
THAT MAKES IT SEEM LIKE
ALL YOU HAVE TO DO

22:38.558 --> 22:41.027
IS POP SOME PILL
AND YOU'RE AS GOOD AS NEW.

22:41.060 --> 22:42.462
ANYBODY WHO'S EVER
TAKEN ONE KNOWS

22:42.495 --> 22:45.398
WHAT A CROCK OF SHIT
THAT IS.

22:59.679 --> 23:04.651
[laughter]

23:08.788 --> 23:13.392
[groaning and laughter]

23:21.534 --> 23:24.904
- MUSHROOM?

23:24.937 --> 23:28.441
- SURE, WHY NOT?

23:28.475 --> 23:32.912
- * YOU SET FOOT IN THE FOREST

23:32.945 --> 23:37.183
* BUT YOUR MIND'S SET
IN CONCRETE *

23:37.216 --> 23:41.688
* STILL YOU TRY
TO GET BACK TO NATURE *

23:41.721 --> 23:45.925
* BUT YOU'RE LONGING
FOR THE STREETS *

23:45.958 --> 23:51.197
* OF NEW YORK CITY,
OH, THE CITY *

23:51.230 --> 23:55.001
* TO MAKE YOU FEEL COMPLETE

23:55.034 --> 24:00.006
* LIKE A REFINED YOUNG MAN

24:00.039 --> 24:02.742
* IN THE JUNGLES

24:02.775 --> 24:04.977
*

24:05.011 --> 24:09.015
* YOU THINK
YOU WANT TO BE HERE *

24:09.048 --> 24:14.554
* IT LOOKED GOOD
IN THE MAGAZINE *

24:14.587 --> 24:18.758
* TO GET IN TOUCH
WITH YOUR PRIMAL SELF *

24:18.791 --> 24:22.962
* A GARDEN OF EDEN SCENE

24:22.995 --> 24:27.266
* LIKE A REFINED YOUNG MAN

24:27.299 --> 24:30.136
* IN THE JUNGLES

24:30.169 --> 24:32.872
*

24:32.905 --> 24:40.647
* OOH, AHH

24:40.680 --> 24:46.252
* OOH

24:46.285 --> 24:54.126
* OH, OH, OH

24:54.160 --> 25:02.134
* OOH

25:02.168 --> 25:05.638
- HEY, LOOKING FOR
THE NAKED TWISTER COMPETITION?

25:05.672 --> 25:08.608
- PROBABLY THE LAST THING
I'M LOOKING FOR.

25:08.641 --> 25:12.211
- THEN, UH, HOW ABOUT
GIVING ME A HAND, DARLING?

25:12.244 --> 25:14.280
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

25:14.313 --> 25:16.816
- IMPORTANT WORK.

25:18.918 --> 25:20.887
- MOVING ROCKS?

25:20.920 --> 25:23.690
- DEPENDS ON WHY
YOU'RE MOVING THEM.

25:23.723 --> 25:27.594
HERE, HELP ME
PLACE THEM IN A CIRCLE.

25:34.066 --> 25:37.169
YOU'RE A NEW FAIRY,
AREN'T YA?

25:37.203 --> 25:39.672
- AROUND HERE,
I SUPPOSE I AM.

25:39.706 --> 25:41.774
- WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

25:41.808 --> 25:43.109
- EMMETT.

25:43.142 --> 25:45.678
- NO, I DON'T MEAN
YOUR MUNDANE NAME.

25:45.712 --> 25:51.350
BACK THERE, I'M HARRY,
BUT HERE, I'M ARIEL.

25:51.383 --> 25:54.654
SO WHAT'S YOUR FAIRY NAME?

25:54.687 --> 25:56.222
- I HAVEN'T THOUGHT OF ONE.

25:56.255 --> 25:58.825
- WHAT'S STOPPING YOU?

25:58.858 --> 26:00.326
- I DON'T KNOW.

26:00.359 --> 26:02.361
- I DO.
- [grunts]

26:02.394 --> 26:05.097
- YOU DON'T BELIEVE
IN FAIRIES.

26:05.131 --> 26:08.334
YOU THINK THIS
IS ALL NONSENSE, DON'T YA?

26:08.367 --> 26:12.739
- NO!
I DON'T, REALLY.

26:12.772 --> 26:15.708
YEAH, I DO.
- [laughs]

26:15.742 --> 26:18.344
WELL, MAYBE WHEN YOU STOP
THINKING THAT WAY,

26:18.377 --> 26:20.112
YOUR FAIRY NAME
WILL COME TO YOU.

26:20.146 --> 26:22.682
- [grunts]

26:22.715 --> 26:27.720
- BUT SOMEHOW,
I DOUBT IT.

26:27.754 --> 26:31.223
YOU SEE, DARLING,
I CAN ALWAYS TELL.

26:31.257 --> 26:35.094
YOU'RE NOT ONE OF US,
A PROUD FAIRY.

